workflows.build.yml:
name: Build Minecraft Mod

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main
  release:
    types: [published]

env:
  JAVA_VERSION: '21'
  GRADLE_BUILD_TASK: 'build'
  ARTIFACT_STAGING_DIR: './artifacts_to_upload'

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Repository
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup Java
        uses: actions/setup-java@v4
        with:
          distribution: 'temurin'
          java-version: ${{ env.JAVA_VERSION }}
          cache: 'gradle'

      - name: Grant Execute Permissions for Gradle Wrapper
        run: chmod +x gradlew

      - name: Build Mod
        run: ./gradlew ${{ env.GRADLE_BUILD_TASK }}

      - name: Create Staging Directory
        run: mkdir -p ${{ env.ARTIFACT_STAGING_DIR }}

      - name: Collect and Rename JARs
        run: |
          find versions -type f -path "*/build/libs/*.jar" \
            ! -name "*-sources.jar" \
            ! -name "*-javadoc.jar" | while read -r jar_path; do

            mc_version=$(echo "$jar_path" | sed -n 's|versions/\([^/]*\)/.*|\1|p')

            original_filename=$(basename "$jar_path")

            new_filename="${mc_version}-${original_filename}"

            echo "Renaming '$original_filename' (from MC $mc_version) to '$new_filename'"

            # Copy and rename to the staging directory
            cp "$jar_path" "${{ env.ARTIFACT_STAGING_DIR }}/$new_filename"
          done

      - name: List Staged Files
        run: ls -l ${{ env.ARTIFACT_STAGING_DIR }}

      - name: Upload JARs
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: mod-jars
          path: ${{ env.ARTIFACT_STAGING_DIR }}/
          retention-days: 7

  release:
    if: github.event_name == 'release' && github.event.action == 'published'
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    needs: build

    steps:
      - name: Download JARs
        uses: actions/download-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: mod-jars

      - name: List Downloaded Files
        run: ls -R

      - name: Create Release
        id: create_release
        uses: softprops/action-gh-release@v1
        with:
          files: "*.jar"
          prerelease: ${{ contains(github.ref_name, 'beta') || contains(github.ref_name, 'rc') }}
        env:
          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}

gradle.properties:
# When declaring a String list use spaces between values I.E: value1 value2 value3 value4 ...
# Note: Some string lists have optional parameters, use "UNSET" to denote them.

# Done to increase the memory available to gradle.
org.gradle.jvmargs=-Xmx3G
org.gradle.parallel=true

# Basic gradle constants, should match the src directory.
# Defaults to mod.id
archives_base_name = UNSET
# Defaults to com.[authors]
group = UNSET
version = 0.0.1

# Display name is for user display, id is for programmatic identification.
# $start config-name
mod.display_name = Example Mod
# $end config-name
# $start config-id
mod.id = example_mod
# $end config-id
# $start config-class
mod.class_name = ExampleMod
# $end config-class

# Edit these to fit your mod
# $start config-license
mod.license = MIT
# $end config-license
# $start config-description
mod.description = TODO! TODO! TODO!
# $end config-description
# $start config-author
mod.authors = author
# $end config-author
mod.source_url=https://github.com/Drathonix/rockbreaker
mod.issue_tracker=https://github.com/Drathonix/rockbreaker/issues
mod.icon=icon.png
# Will use source_url by default
mod.general_website=UNSET

# When true mixins.${id}.json will be included in the resulting jar.
mixins.vanilla.enable = true
# When true mixins.fabric.${id}.json will be included in the resulting jar.
mixins.fabric.enable = false
# When true mixins.forge.${id}.json will be included in the resulting jar.
mixins.forge.enable = false
# When true mixins.neoforge.${id}.json will be included in the resulting jar.
mixins.neoforge.enable = false
# Includes extra mixins if specified, must be in String list format
mixins.extras = UNSET

# Core dependency versions
# These are critical by mod loader.

# This is a Version Range, a 1-2 argument String List where arg0 is the minimum version and arg1 is the maximum. The maximum version can be UNSET
# Version range minimum will be used as the dev-env version.
deps.core.mc.version_range=[VERSIONED]

# Version ranges are INCLUSIVE! The minimum version must be set, this is the value used to retrieve the dependency from network.
// $start config-fabric-range
deps.core.fabric.loader.version_range= [VERSIONED]
// $end config-fabric-range
deps.core.forge.version_range=[VERSIONED]
deps.core.neoforge.version_range=[VERSIONED]
deps.core.neoforge.loader.version_range=2 UNSET

# Load before - if present our mod will load before these.
# format of mod1 mod2 mod3 ...
deps.before = UNSET

# Controls publishing automation
# Set to false when publishing for real.
publish.dry_run = true
# Leaving this field unset will use the mc_min value.
# To specify versions use the format ver1 ver2 ver3 ...
publish.acceptable_mc_versions = UNSET
publish.token.modrinth = UNSET
publish.token.curseforge = UNSET
# You must also have the credentials stored in Environment Variables.
# The environment vars are MVN_NAME and MVN_PASSWORD
publish.maven.url = UNSET
